            "creation_date": 1520264347,
            "body": "<p><code>sentence<\/code> is never modified, Strings are immutable, <code>replace<\/code> returns a new String every time.<\/p>\n\n<p>You need to do it this way:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>tempPhrase = sentence.replace('.' , ' ')\n    .replace(',' , ' ')\n    .replace('!' , ' ')\n    .replace('?' , ' ')\n    .replace(':' , ' ')\n    .replace(';' , ' ');\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>or<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>tempPhrase1 = sentence.replace('.' , ' ');\ntempPhrase2 = tempPhrase1.replace(',' , ' ');\ntempPhrase3 = tempPhrase2.replace('!' , ' ');\ntempPhrase4 = tempPhrase3.replace('?' , ' ');\ntempPhrase5 = tempPhrase4.replace(':' , ' ');\ntempPhrase = tempPhrase5.replace(';' , ' ');\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 49114080,
            "question_id": 49114047,
            "last_edit_date": 1520264808
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/Fp3hB.jpg?s=256",
